   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"0\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Workspace SDK Examples\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook demonstrates how to work with Evo Workspaces using the **Evo Python SDK**, providing a simplified and streamlined experience for common workspace operations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### SDK vs API Approach\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook uses the **Workspace SDK (WorkspaceAPIClient)** which:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- ✅ Simplified method calls with minimal boilerplate code\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- ✅ Automatic handling of complex API interactions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- ✅ Better error handling and validation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- ✅ Type hints and IDE autocomplete support\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- ✅ Recommended for most common use cases\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Want More Control Over API Requests?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"If you need granular control over API requests and want to see detailed response structures, check out the `api-examples.ipynb` notebook in this same directory. The API examples show:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Direct API calls using the connector\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Full control over request/response handling\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Detailed API response structures and metadata\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Useful for debugging and advanced use cases\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"1\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import os\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import sys; sys.path.insert(0, \\\"..\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from auth_helper import get_manual_auth\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.common import APIConnector\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import WorkspaceAPIClient\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"cache_location = \\\"./notebook-data\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"input_path = f\\\"{cache_location}/input\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Evo app credentials (uses environment variables in CI, or replace with your own)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"client_id = os.environ.get(\\\"EVO_CLIENT_ID\\\", \\\"<your-client-id>\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"redirect_url = os.environ.get(\\\"EVO_REDIRECT_URL\\\", \\\"<your-redirect-url>\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"org_id = os.environ.get(\\\"EVO_ORG_ID\\\", \\\"<your-organization-id>\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"hub_url = os.environ.get(\\\"EVO_HUB_URL\\\", \\\"<your-hub-url>\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"client_name = \\\"Evo Python SDK Notebook Example\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"transport, authorizer, org_id, hub_url = await get_manual_auth(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    client_id=client_id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    redirect_url=redirect_url,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    org_id=org_id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    hub_url=hub_url,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    user_agent=client_name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"2\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Create the Workspace API client\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"3\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"workspace_client = WorkspaceAPIClient(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    connector=APIConnector(hub_url, transport, authorizer),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    org_id=org_id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"4\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Workspace operations\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"5\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### List all workspaces\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"If you have access to less than 50 workspaces it's easier to list all workspaces in a single request.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"6\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import Workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    all_workspaces: list[Workspace] = await workspace_client.list_all_workspaces()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Display the workspaces in a table\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    workspace_list = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            \\\"Name\\\": workspace.display_name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            \\\"ID\\\": workspace.id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            \\\"User Role\\\": workspace.user_role,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        }\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        for workspace in all_workspaces\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df = pd.DataFrame(workspace_list)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    display(df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error listing workspaces:\\\\n{e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"7\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### List paginated workspaces\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"If you have access to more than 50 workspaces, it may be more convenient to work with a paginated list of workspaces. By changing the `limit` and `offset` values each time to make the request, you can efficiently iterate through your workspaces.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"8\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from evo.common import Page\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import Workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    paginated_workspaces: Page[Workspace] = await workspace_client.list_workspaces(limit=5, offset=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Create workspace list from paginated results\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    workspace_list = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            \\\"Name\\\": workspace.display_name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            \\\"ID\\\": workspace.id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            \\\"User Role\\\": workspace.user_role,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        }\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        for workspace in paginated_workspaces.items()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df = pd.DataFrame(workspace_list)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    display(df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error listing workspaces:\\\\n{e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"9\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Create a workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Workspaces can be created with an optional bounding box, which is a polygon shape made up of a list of longitude and latitude coordinates. \\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Important note:** The first and last coordinate must be identical. \\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Workspaces can also be created with an optional coordinate reference system.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"10\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import Workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    new_workspace: Workspace = await workspace_client.create_workspace(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        name=\\\"My new workspace\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        description=\\\"This is a new workspace\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        bounding_box_coordinates=[\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            (85.8287, -90.0),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            (85.8287, 69.84278),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            (-180.0, 69.84278),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            (-180.0, -90.0),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            (85.8287, -90.0),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        ],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        default_coordinate_system=\\\"EPSG:2134\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Display the workspace details\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    workspace_info = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Name\\\": new_workspace.display_name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"ID\\\": new_workspace.id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Description\\\": new_workspace.description,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"User Role\\\": new_workspace.user_role,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Created At\\\": new_workspace.created_at,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    }\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df = pd.DataFrame([workspace_info]).T\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df.columns = [\\\"Workspace info\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    display(df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error creating workspace: {e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"11\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Fetch details for a specific workspace\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"12\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import Workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    workspace: Workspace = await workspace_client.get_workspace(workspace_id=new_workspace.id)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Display the workspace details\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    workspace_info = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Name\\\": workspace.display_name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"ID\\\": workspace.id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"User Role\\\": workspace.user_role,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    }\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df = pd.DataFrame([workspace_info]).T\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df.columns = [\\\"Workspace info\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    display(df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error listing workspaces:\\\\n{e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"13\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Update a workspace\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"14\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import Workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    updated_workspace: Workspace = await workspace_client.update_workspace(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        workspace_id=new_workspace.id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        name=\\\"My updated workspace\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        description=\\\"This is an updated workspace\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Display the updated workspace details\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    workspace_info = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Name\\\": updated_workspace.display_name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"ID\\\": updated_workspace.id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Description\\\": updated_workspace.description,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"User Role\\\": updated_workspace.user_role,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Created At\\\": updated_workspace.created_at,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    }\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df = pd.DataFrame([workspace_info]).T\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df.columns = [\\\"Workspace info\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    display(df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error updating workspace: {e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"15\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## User operations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Users can be added to a workspace with one of three user roles:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Owner\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Editor\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Viewer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Workspace roles follow these rules:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Users who have the owner role in a workspace can add users with any one of the three roles.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Users who have the editor role in a workspace can add users with the either the editor or the viewer role.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Users who have the viewer role can't add other users to a workspace.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"To change a user's role in a workspace you must know both the ID of the workspace and the ID of the user.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"16\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Fetch details of the current user's workspace role\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Get the role of the currently authenticated user in a specific workspace.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"17\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import UserRole\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    user_role: UserRole = await workspace_client.get_current_user_role(workspace_id=new_workspace.id)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error retrieving user role:\\\\n{e}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Current user's role in workspace '{new_workspace.display_name}': {user_role.role}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"18\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### List users with access to a workspace\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"19\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import User\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    users: list[User] = await workspace_client.list_user_roles(workspace_id=new_workspace.id)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Display the users details\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    user_roles_list = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        {\\\"Full name\\\": user.full_name, \\\"Email\\\": user.email, \\\"Role\\\": user.role, \\\"User ID\\\": user.user_id} for user in users\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df = pd.DataFrame(user_roles_list)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    display(df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error listing users in this workspace:\\\\n{e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"20\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Assign a user to a workspace\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"21\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import uuid\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import WorkspaceRole\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    new_users_role: UserRole = await workspace_client.assign_user_role(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        workspace_id=new_workspace.id, user_id=uuid.UUID(\\\"<some-user-id>\\\"), role=WorkspaceRole.viewer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error assigning user role:\\\\n{e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"22\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Remove a user from a workspace\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"23\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import uuid\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    await workspace_client.delete_user_role(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        workspace_id=new_workspace.id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        user_id=uuid.UUID(\\\"<some-user-id>\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error removing user role:\\\\n{e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"24\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Delete a workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"When you delete a workspace, it will be soft-deleted. Deleted workspaces will no longer be accessible through `list_all_workspaces` by default.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The `delete_workspace` function has no return value.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"25\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    await workspace_client.delete_workspace(workspace_id=new_workspace.id)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Successfully deleted workspace: {new_workspace.display_name}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Error deleting workspace: {e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"26\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Fetch details of a deleted workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"You must include the `deleted=True` option to find details of a deleted workspace.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"27\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from evo.workspaces import Workspace\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    workspace: Workspace = await workspace_client.get_workspace(workspace_id=new_workspace.id, deleted=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Display the workspace details\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    workspace_info = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Name\\\": workspace.display_name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"ID\\\": workspace.id,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"User Role\\\": workspace.user_role,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    }\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    df = pd.DataFrame([workspace_info]).T\\n\",\n",
